Training Complex for AI Agent Developer & Integrator: From Zero to Practitioner (AI Agent Developer & Integrator)
Prerequisite: Knowledge of LLM architecture, prompt construction, and prompt engineering skills required.
Date compiled: 20.02.2026
Concept: Achieve the necessary proficiency in Python, APIs, RAG, and then proceed directly to AI agent development, with a focus on practical integration into business processes. The experimental block—research on agent swarms—is designated as a separate advanced step. This block should provide reviews of new products, help analyze code from complex third-party projects, suggest experiments to deepen topic understanding, highlight non-obvious challenges in architecture design, agent interaction, coordination, and other complex aspects.
________________________________________
Structure of the Complex
The complex will consist of several blocks:
1.	**Methodologist **(Coach) – Coordinator who analyzes reports from other blocks, maintains the progress map, and plans next steps.
2.	Python Instructor – Responsible for immersion into the language.
3.	API Instructor – Responsible for working with APIs, including LLMs and Russian services.
4.	RAG Instructor – Responsible for Retrieval-Augmented Generation systems.
5.	AI Agent Development & Integration Instructor – Core course on agents.
6.	Agent Swarm Researcher – Experimental block for advanced study.
